sql:
SELECT DISTINCT product_name
FROM products
ORDER BY product_name ASC;

external_knowledge:
- The term "top loyalty program customers" refers to those customers with the highest loyalty points in each loyalty points category;
- "Loyalty points" is a measure of customer loyalty, with higher points indicating greater loyalty;
- "Loyalty program details" include the program name and loyalty points earned by the customer;
- "Maximum purchase amount" is the highest amount spent by a customer in a single purchase;
- "Total amount spent" is the total amount spent by a customer across all purchases;
- "Purchase count" is the number of purchases made by a customer;
- "Preferences" refer to the customer's marketing preferences, such as email or SMS marketing.
